<br>
Turned in all the pieces to the wyvern and got back the Finished Naginata.  Now I just have to spend some time in Siren's Grotto to get a couple of flawless diamonds and it will be time to rev up the guild and grab a few folks to go kill the dragons.<br>
<br>
So let me make sure I have this straight.  <br>
<br>
1) I say the phrase: &quot;You are one but two. Your vengeance shall find a home.&quot;  I say this standing on the bone pile in the same spot I said &quot;Remember, Garzicor&quot;.<br>
<br>
2) I give the &quot;Ghostly Presence&quot; the Kromzek Blood when he spawns, being careful that he is, indeed, the one I am giving it to.  That causes Garzicor's Remains to spawn.<br>
<br>
3) Garzicor's Remains attacks me.  I kill him and he is relatively easy.<br>
<br>
4) Once Garzicor's Remains is killed, another ghostly dragon appears, &quot;Garzicor's Wrath&quot; and I have to kill it too. He's tougher with a strong Fear AoE.<br>
<br>
5) Once he dies, two more translucent dragons spawn that are on CoV faction, one at the original spot and one farther down the tunnel. I give each a flawless diamond in turn and receive back a &quot;Magical Blackened Diamond&quot; from each.<br>
<br>
6) I go to a forge, combine the two Magical Blackened Diamonds with the Finished Naginata. (Heaven help me if I fail THAT combine!)<br>
<br>
7) I take the final blade to Eldriaks Fe'Dhar and give it to him. He gives it back and I have finally receive the Ethereal Bladed Naginata....FINALLY!<br>
<br>
Did I miss anything???  That final hand in to Eldriaks is necessary? Or no? I'm after the weapon, not the earring or other item.<br>
<br>
Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>
